---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Redactorizer"
  description="Redactorizer privacy policy. How we handle your data on the website and in the app."
  current="privacy"
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-20">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-normal tracking-tight text-fg sm:text-4xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-fg-muted">
        Last updated: February 12, 2025
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-fg-muted">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">The Redactorizer app</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          Redactorizer is designed around privacy. <strong class="text-fg">All redaction happens locally on your Mac.</strong> No documents, images, or other data are ever sent to our servers or any third party. Nothing leaves your computer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">This website</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          The Redactorizer website (redactorizer.com) provides information about the app and ways to contact us. We collect minimal data:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
          <li><strong class="text-fg">Contact emails</strong> — If you email us (for example, to request a free copy or ask a question), we receive your email address and message. We use this only to respond and do not share it with third parties.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-fg">Fonts</strong> — We use Google Fonts to display typefaces. Your browser may request fonts from Google’s servers; Google’s privacy policy applies to that request.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-fg">Hosting</strong> — Our hosting provider may log standard server data (IP address, request timestamps, etc.) for security and operations. We do not use this for analytics or tracking.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Mac App Store</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          If you purchase Redactorizer through the Mac App Store, Apple processes the transaction. Apple’s privacy policy and terms apply to that purchase. We do not receive payment details or personal information from Apple beyond what’s required for sales reporting.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Cookies and analytics</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          We do not use cookies, analytics, or tracking on this website. We do not sell or share your data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the top reflects the most recent version. Continued use of the website or app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-fg">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
          For questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, contact us at <a href="mailto:jason@10layer.com" class="text-accent transition hover:text-accent-hover focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-accent focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-surface rounded">jason@10layer.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
